---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog — Rupadana">
  <section class="hero reveal">
    <h1>Notes on systems, tools, and useful software.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A small place for technical writing, ideas, and practical notes on building products,
      backend systems, and developer workflows.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="article-list reveal">
    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Tools</span>
      <h2>Shinobi NVR: Open-Source CCTV Solution Based on Node.js</h2>
      <p>
        Building a lightweight, modern, and flexible self-hosted surveillance system with Shinobi NVR.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/shinobi-nvr-solusi-cctv-open-source">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Cybersecurity</span>
      <h2>CEH v13: Ethical Hacking in the Age of AI</h2>
      <p>
        An overview of the new Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH) v13 AI and why the integration of Artificial Intelligence is a major shift for security professionals.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/ceh-v13-ethical-hacking-in-the-age-of-ai">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Security</span>
      <h2>Webhook Security: How to Secure Your Endpoints</h2>
      <p>
        A guide to verifying, protecting, and hardening your webhook endpoints against unauthorized access and payload tampering.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/webhook-security-best-practices">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">AI Infrastructure</span>
      <h2>Model Context Protocol (MCP): The Universal Connector for AI</h2>
      <p>
        How Anthropic's new open standard is solving the "data silo" problem and transforming how AI models interact with your tools and data.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/mcp-universal-connector-for-ai">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">System Design</span>
      <h2>Idempotency: The Secret to Reliable API Design</h2>
      <p>
        Why doing the same thing twice shouldn't break your system. A guide to building resilient APIs in distributed environments.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/idempotency-reliable-api-design">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">AI</span>
      <h2>Qwen 2.5: The Open-Source LLM Powerhouse</h2>
      <p>
        A deep dive into Alibaba's latest model series, featuring the breakthrough 1M token context window and frontier-level coding capabilities.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/qwen-2-5-open-source-llm-powerhouse">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">AI Tools</span>
      <h2>Google AI Studio: A Free Developer Playground for Gemini API</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way to experiment with Gemini models — straight from your browser, at no cost and with no credit card required.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/google-ai-studio-playground-gratis-gemini-api">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Networking</span>
      <h2>Cloudflare Tunnel: Expose Your Server Without Opening a Single Port</h2>
      <p>
        The simplest way to self-host securely — no port forwarding, no exposed IP, automatic SSL, and built-in DDoS protection.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/cloudflare-tunnel-expose-server-without-open-ports">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Process Management</span>
      <h2>PM2: The Powerful Process Manager for Node.js and Python</h2>
      <p>
        How to keep your web applications alive and performant in production — auto-restart, monitoring, and zero-downtime reloads.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/pm2-process-manager">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">AI</span>
      <h2>Alibaba Cloud Model Studio: 1M Free Tokens</h2>
      <p>
        Explore the powerful Qwen model series with Alibaba's generous free tier and revolutionary 1M context length.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/alibaba-cloud-model-studio-1m-free-tokens">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">AI</span>
      <h2>Antigravity: The Future of Agentic AI Coding</h2>
      <p>
        Beyond simple chatbots: An inside look at the powerful framework powering the next generation of AI assistants.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/antigravity-the-future-of-agentic-coding">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Tools</span>
      <h2>code-server: VS Code in the Browser</h2>
      <p>
        Run VS Code on any remote server and access it from any device with a web browser.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/code-server-vscode-in-the-browser">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">No-Code</span>
      <h2>NocoDB: Open-Source Airtable Alternative</h2>
      <p>
        Turn any SQL database into a smart spreadsheet with full collaboration features and instant APIs.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/nocodb-open-source-airtable-alternative">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">Data</span>
      <h2>Metabase: Business Intelligence Made Easy</h2>
      <p>
        Make data-driven decisions without needing to be an SQL expert. An introduction to the most popular open-source BI tool.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/metabase-business-intelligence-made-easy">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">API</span>
      <h2>Hoppscotch: Lightweight API Testing</h2>
      <p>
        A fast, web-native, and open-source API development suite designed for modern workflows.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/hoppscotch-lightweight-api-testing">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">AI Tools</span>
      <h2>Exploring Antigravity Claude Proxy</h2>
      <p>
        How to use Anthropic's Claude Code CLI for free by proxying requests through Google's GenAI infrastructure—and the risks involved.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/antigravity-claude-proxy">Read article →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="tag">OpenClaw</span>
      <h2>What is OpenClaw?</h2>
      <p>
        A practical introduction to OpenClaw: what it is, how it works, and why it matters for people
        who want a self-hosted AI assistant they can actually message from anywhere.
      </p>
      <a class="inline-link" href="/blog/what-is-openclaw">Read article →</a>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
.article-list {
  display: grid;
  gap: 18px;
  padding: 24px 0 56px;
}
.card h2 {
  margin: 14px 0 10px;
}
</style>
